.SH "NAME"
dtkarc \- DTKA user configuration commands file
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\s-1DTKA\s0 user configuration commands are passed to \fBdtkaadmin\fR either
in a file of text lines or interactively at \fBdtkaadmin\fR's command prompt
(:).  Commands are interpreted line-by line, with exactly one command per
line.  The formats and effects of the \s-1DTKA\s0 user function administration
commands are described below.
.SH "COMMANDS"
.IX Header "COMMANDS"
.IP "\fB?\fR" 4
.IX Item "?"
The \fBhelp\fR command.  This will display a listing of the commands and their
formats.  It is the same as the \fBh\fR command.
.IP "\fB#\fR" 4
.IX Item "#"
Comment line.  Lines beginning with \fB#\fR are not interpreted.
.IP "\fBe\fR { 1 | 0 }" 4
.IX Item "e { 1 | 0 }"
Echo control.  Setting echo to 1 causes all output printed by dtkaadmin to be
logged as well as sent to stdout.  Setting echo to 0 disables this behavior.
.IP "\fB1\fR" 4
.IX Item "1"
The \fBinitialize\fR command.  Until this command is executed, the \s-1DTKA\s0 user
function is not in operation on the local \s-1ION\s0 node and most \fIdtkaadmin\fR
commands will fail.
.IP "\fBi\fR" 4
.IX Item "i"
The \fBinfo\fR This command will print information about the current state
of the local node's \s-1DTKA\s0 user function, including the current settings of
all parameters that can be managed as described below.
.IP "\fBm keygentime\fR \fItime\fR" 4
.IX Item "m keygentime time"
The \fBmanage key generation time\fR command.  This command sets the time at
which the node will next generate a public/private key pair and multicast
the public key.  The command is not needed in normal operations, because
future key generation times are computed automatically as key pairs are
generated. \fItime\fR must be in yyyy/mm/dd\-hh:mm:ss format.
.IP "\fBm interval\fR \fIkey_pair_generation_interval\fR" 4
.IX Item "m interval key_pair_generation_interval"
The \fBmanage key pair generation interval\fR command.  This interval,
expressed as a number of seconds, controls the period on which the \s-1DTKA\s0
user function will generate new public/private key pairs.  The default
value is 604800 (one week).
.IP "\fBm leadtime\fR \fIkey_pair_effectivenes_lead_time\fR" 4
.IX Item "m leadtime key_pair_effectivenes_lead_time"
The \fBmanage key pair effectivenes lead time\fR command.  This interval,
expressed as a number of seconds, controls the length of time after the
time of key pair generation at which the key pair will become effective.
The default value is 345600 (four days).
.IP "\fBh\fR" 4
.IX Item "h"
The \fBhelp\fR command.  This will display a listing of the commands and their
formats.  It is the same as the \fB?\fR command.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.IX Header "EXAMPLES"
.IP "m interval 3600" 4
.IX Item "m interval 3600"
Asserts that the \s-1DTKA\s0 function will generate a new key pair every 3600 seconds
(one hour).
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
